var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"autograd/#Autograd","page":"Autograd","text":"Wraps matrices / vectors in AValue, builds an expression, and calls backward! to populate the gradients of every node in the graph:\n\nusing MicroGPT\n\nW = AValue([1.0 2.0; 3.0 4.0])\nx = AValue([5.0, 6.0])\n\ny = W * x\nloss = sum(relu(y))\nbackward!(loss)","title":"Autograd"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#API-reference","page":"API reference","text":"","title":"API reference"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#MicroGPT.AValue","page":"API reference","text":"AValue{D<:AbstractArray, G<:AbstractArray, P<:Tuple, F}\n\nNode in a vector-based automatic differentiation graph.\n\nEach node stores its forward value data, accumulated gradient grad,  its parent nodes parents and a pullback function pullback_fn that is  used during reverse-mode automatic differentiation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.AValue"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.AValue-Tuple{T} where T<:AbstractArray","page":"API reference","text":"AValue{val::T}\n\nConstructor for an AValue leaf node.\n\nReturns a node holding value val, zero grads, no parents and empty  pullback function.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.AValue"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#MicroGPT.Adam","page":"API reference","text":"Adam <: Optimizer\n\nState for an Adam optimizer over a flat list of AValue parameters.\n\nHolds the parameters being optimized along with the hyperparameters and the per-parameter moment buffers that Àdam maintains across step! calls.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.Adam"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.Adam-Tuple{Vector{<:AValue}}","page":"API reference","text":"Adam(params; α=0.01, β1=0.85, β2=0.99, ϵ=1e-8)\n\nBuild an Adam optimizer over a flat list of AValue parameters.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.Adam"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#MicroGPT.Tokenizer","page":"API reference","text":"Tokenizer\n\nA character-level tokenizer built from a corpus of documents.\n\nFields:\n\nuchars: sorted, deduplicated vocabulary characters.\nchar2id: reverse lookup from character to its token ID.\nbos: boundary token ID used to wrap every encoded sequence.\nvocab_size: number of distinct tokens, including the bos token.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.Tokenizer"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.Tokenizer-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:AbstractString}}","page":"API reference","text":"Tokenizer(docs::AbstractVector{<:AbstractString})\n\nBuild a Tokenizer from docs. The vocabulary is the sorted set of all characters appearing in the corpus.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.Tokenizer"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.backward!-Tuple{AValue}","page":"API reference","text":"backward!(v::AValue)\n\nComputes the gradients of v with respect to every AValue in its computation graph via backpropagation.\n\nThis mutates all gradients in the computational graph. Gradients are accumulated, so zeroing the gradients is required between passes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.backward!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.decode-Tuple{Tokenizer, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"API reference","text":"decode(tok::Tokenizer, ids::AbstractVector{<:Integer}) -> String\n\nDecode token IDs back into a string, stripping boundary tokens. Throws ArgumentError if ids contains an ID outside the vocabulary.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.decode"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.div_elementwise-Tuple{AValue, AValue}","page":"API reference","text":"div_elementwise(a::AValue, b::AValue)\n\nDivides two AValues (a and b) elementwise. Both arguments  must be of same shape.\n\nReturns a new AValue type holding the elementwise division.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.div_elementwise"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.encode-Tuple{Tokenizer, AbstractString}","page":"API reference","text":"encode(tok::Tokenizer, doc::AbstractString) -> Vector{Int}\n\nEncode doc into token IDs, wrapped with the boundary token at both ends. Throws ArgumentError if doc contains a character outside the vocabulary.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.encode"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.linear-Tuple{AValue, AValue}","page":"API reference","text":"linear(x::AValue, W::AValue)\n\nApplies a linear transformation to AValue x using weight matrix W.\n\nReturns a new AValue type holding the transformed output. (Hint: Docstring generated with https://chatgpt.com/share/6a3fcb2d-0ecc-83eb-9e40-c00c1661c295)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.linear"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#MicroGPT.load_data","page":"API reference","text":"load_data(path=\"input.txt\"; shuffle=true, rng=Random.default_rng()) -> Vector{String}\n\nLoad a corpus of documents, one per non-empty line of path, with surrounding whitespace stripped.\n\nIf path does not exist, the names dataset is downloaded to path first. When shuffle is true the documents are shuffled in place using rng.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.load_data"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.mul_elementwise-Tuple{AValue, AValue}","page":"API reference","text":"mul_elementwise(a::AValue, b::AValue)\n\nMultiplies two AValues (a and b) elementwise. Both arguments  must be of same shape.\n\nReturns a new AValue type holding the elementwise multiplication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.mul_elementwise"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.pow_elementwise_scalar-Tuple{AValue, Real}","page":"API reference","text":"pow_elementwise_scalar(a::AValue, b::Real)\n\nPotentiates an AValue a by a scalar b elementwise.\n\nReturns a new AValue type holding the elementwise potentiation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.pow_elementwise_scalar"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.relu-Tuple{AValue}","page":"API reference","text":"relu(a::AValue)\n\nApplies elementwise ReLU to AValue a.\n\nReturns a new AValue type holding the elementwise ReLU.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.relu"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.rmsnorm-Tuple{AValue{<:AbstractVector}}","page":"API reference","text":"rmsnorm(x::AValue{<:AbstractVector}; eps::Float64 = 1e-5)\n\nApplies RMS normalization to AValue vector x.\n\nReturns a new AValue type holding the RMS-normalized vector. (Hint: Docstring generated with https://chatgpt.com/share/6a3fcb2d-0ecc-83eb-9e40-c00c1661c295)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.rmsnorm"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.softmax-Tuple{AValue{<:AbstractVector}}","page":"API reference","text":"softmax(x::AValue{<:AbstractVector})\n\nApplies the softmax function to AValue vector x.\n\nReturns a new AValue type holding the softmax probabilities. (Hint: Docstring generated with https://chatgpt.com/share/6a3fcb2d-0ecc-83eb-9e40-c00c1661c295)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.softmax"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.step!-Tuple{Adam}","page":"API reference","text":"step!(opt::Adam)\n\nOne Adam update step over all AValue parameters, elementwise per array. Assumes gradients have been updated before executing.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.step!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#MicroGPT.zero_grad!-Tuple{MicroGPT.Optimizer}","page":"API reference","text":"zero_grad!(opt::Optimizer)\n\nSet the shared gradients of opt to zero.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"MicroGPT.zero_grad!"},{"category":"section","location":"#MicroGPT","page":"Home","text":"Documentation for MicroGPT.\n\nMicroGPT.jl is a minimal, educational re-implementation of the building blocks of a GPT-style model in pure Julia, inspired by Andrej Karpathys microgpt: a scalar reverse-mode autograd engine, a character-level tokenizer, and a small dataset loader.","title":"MicroGPT"},{"category":"section","location":"#Getting-started","page":"Home","text":"Install the package directly from GitHub (press ] in the REPL to enter package mode):\n\npkg> add https://github.com/patrickzda/MicroGPT.jl\n\nFrom here, see the Tokenizer and Autograd guides for usage examples, and the API reference for the full list of exported functions.","title":"Getting started"},{"category":"section","location":"optimizer/#Optimizer","page":"Optimizer","text":"The optimizer updates the parameters of a model from the gradients computed by the Autograd engine. MicroGPT provides Adam, which maintains per-parameter moment estimates across update steps. See the original paper, Adam: A Method for Stochastic Optimization, for the underlying algorithm.\n\nA training step has three parts: zero the gradients with zero_grad!, run a forward/backward pass to populate them (see backward!), and apply one update with step!.\n\nEach call to step! advances the optimizer's timestep, which is used for the bias correction of the moment estimates, so the moments accumulated across iterations carry over between steps.","title":"Optimizer"},{"category":"section","location":"optimizer/#Hyperparameters","page":"Optimizer","text":"Adam is constructed from a flat Vector of AValue parameters and accepts the standard Adam hyperparameters as keyword arguments:\n\nKeyword Default Meaning\nα 0.01 learning rate\nβ1 0.85 first-moment decay\nβ2 0.99 second-moment decay\nϵ 1e-8 numerical stabilizer\n\nopt = Adam(params; α=0.001, β1=0.9, β2=0.999)","title":"Hyperparameters"},{"category":"section","location":"tokenizer/#Tokenizer","page":"Tokenizer","text":"Build a character-level Tokenizer from a corpus of documents, then encode a string into token IDs and decode it back. The following example runs during the documentation build:\n\nusing MicroGPT\n\ndocs = [\"emma\", \"olivia\", \"ava\", \"isabella\", \"sophia\"]\ntok = Tokenizer(docs)\n\nids = encode(tok, \"ava\")\n\ndecode(tok, ids)\n\nIn your own code you can load the full names dataset with load_data, which downloads it automatically on first use:\n\ndocs = load_data()\ntok = Tokenizer(docs)","title":"Tokenizer"}]
}
